text: I had a job like this funny enough. I cleaned out hoarders houses. There was one in particular that I‚Äôll never forget. Not only was there a room filled with dolls, as my friend and I was cleaning out the basement, I was taking stuff off of a shelf, and I heard a bunch of stuff shuffling around behind me. I thought it was my friend, so I said something to him, and got no response. Turns out, he hadn‚Äôt been down there for a while cause he was on his break. I was alone. I didn‚Äôt say anything to any of the guys working with me, until they each asked me if I noticed anything weird in the basement. All of us experienced the same thing separately. We looked around and couldn‚Äôt find any evidence of animals. No idea what it was. I have a chronic illness where I don‚Äôt produce cortisol though, so it didn‚Äôt scare me. Nobody else wanted to go down there so I spent hours down there alone, and the shuffling never stopped.
